      "review_summary": "The PR changes `renderTelegramHtmlText` so raw HTML tables in standard Telegram HTML text are converted to `<pre><code>` pipe tables before unsupported-tag escaping.\n\nPR surface: Source +16. Total +16 across 1 file.\n\nReproducibility: yes. Source inspection shows current main's standard HTML renderer passes raw tables to `escapeUnsupportedTelegramHtml`, where legacy Telegram HTML support excludes `table`, and the PR body demonstrates the intended formatter output after the patch.",
