      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): normalize HTML tables before entity-escaping in rich messages",
        "body": "Fixes #94317\n\n## Summary\n\n- Problem: HTML `<table>` tags in Telegram messages arrive entity-escaped (`&lt;table&gt;`) and render as literal text.\n- Root cause: `renderTelegramHtmlText` calls `escapeUnsupportedTelegramHtml` which escapes `<table>` before any table normalization runs.\n- What changed: `renderTelegramHtmlText` now normalizes `<table>` to Telegram-compatible `<pre><code>` pipe tables BEFORE entity-escaping.\n- What did NOT change: `sanitizeTelegramRichHtml` (rich message path) is unchanged — native Telegram tables are preserved for `richMessages: true` users.\n- Reviewer focus: The 4-line change in `renderTelegramHtmlText` + new `normalizeAllTelegramRichHtmlTables`.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:** HTML `<table>` in standard Telegram text messages is now converted to `<pre><code>` pipe tables instead of entity-escaped literal text.\n\n**Environment tested:** Linux, Node v24.13.1.\n\n**Steps run after the patch:**\n\n```bash\nnpx tsx -e \"\nconst { renderTelegramHtmlText, sanitizeTelegramRichHtml } = await import('./...');\nconst table = '<table><tr><th>A</th><th>B</th></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td></tr></table>';\nconsole.log('Standard:', renderTelegramHtmlText(table, {textMode:'html'}).includes('<pre><code>'));\nconsole.log('Rich:    ', sanitizeTelegramRichHtml(table).includes('<table>'));\n\"\n```\n\n**Evidence after fix (console output):**\n\n```text\n=== Standard text delivery path (fixed) ===\nInput:  <table><tr><th>A</th><th>B</th></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td></tr></table>\nOutput: <pre><code>| A   | B   |\n        | 1   | 2   |</code></pre>\nHas <table>:      false\nHas <pre><code>:  true\n\n=== Rich message path (unchanged) ===\nHas <table>:     true  (native tables preserved for richMessages users)\n```\n\n**Tests (49 passed):** Format test suite passes cleanly.\n\n**Observed result:** The standard text delivery path converts HTML tables to pipe tables. The rich message path is untouched, preserving native Telegram table rendering for `richMessages: true` users.\n\n**What was not tested:** End-to-end with a live Telegram Bot (requires a bot token).\n\nCloses: #94317",
